gujarati.context:
The songs of others' love seemed pleasing to us; 
We found the love of our own kin sweet; 
We scrutinized Sri Sukhadai, the lord of our mind; 
And then we reached the state of peaceful calm, O Gangu Bai.

Here is the translation:

Wali dwij bhakt ehe gane, bhaai be budh madari naame;
Bhaje Prabhu prakat pramaan, jaani satsang sachu sujaan.

Here is the translation:

This saying I have settled down to worship with, my mind I offer to do; 
After that in the worship of my mind many hymns are sung by my master saint.
